2. Functions for Exploratory Data Analysis¶

In [7]:
def get_table_categorical(df, col, event='is_in_paid_work', show_heatmap='Y'):
    ''' 
        df - data frame
        col - categorical column name (string) 
        event - event occurance column (1,0)
    '''
    df1 = df[col].value_counts(sort=True).sort_index().reset_index()
    df1.columns = [col,'n']
    df1['% of total'] = df1['n']/df1['n'].sum() * 100

    df2 = df[ df[event]== 1]
    df2 = df2[col].value_counts(sort=True).sort_index().reset_index()
    df2.columns = [col,'In paid work']
    df2['In paid work, % of total'] = df2['In paid work']/df2['In paid work'].sum() * 100

    out = df1.merge(df2, left_on = col, right_on = col)
    cm = sns.light_palette("skyblue", as_cmap=True)
    
    if show_heatmap != 'Y':
        return out
    
    else:
        print('Distribution of 55+ Individuals \nVariable:',event, 'in 2019')
        return out.style.background_gradient(subset=['% of total', 'In paid work, % of total'], cmap=cm)
In [8]:
#  shaded area represents total individuals, black border represents individuals in paid work
def get_histograms(df, col, col_name, col_srt, lower_lim=0, upper_lim=100, plot_width=8, plot_height=6, color='#c6e2ff'):
    
    # Specify plot layout
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(plot_width, plot_height))

    # First histogramzz
    sns.barplot(x=col, y='% of total', data=df, color=color, alpha=1,
                order = df.sort_values(col_srt)[col])
    ax1.set(ylim=(lower_lim, upper_lim), ylabel='% of Total')
    ax1.set(xlabel = col_name)
    
    # Second histogram
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    sns.barplot(x=col, y='In paid work, % of total', data=df,linewidth=2, edgecolor='black', facecolor=(0, 0, 0, 0),  
                order = df.sort_values(col_srt)[col])
    ax2.set(ylim=(lower_lim, upper_lim), ylabel='', yticklabels=[])
    ax2.tick_params(right=False)
    
    if col in bool_cols:
        ax2.xaxis.set_ticks([0,1]) 
        ax2.set_xticklabels(['No', 'Yes'])
    
    ax2.set_title("Impact of "+col_name)
    sns.despine()
    plt.show()
